Clement&#39;s law firm, Bancroft PLLC, was one of nearly two dozen companies that helped sponsor the annual dinner of the Federalist Society, a longtime conservative legal advocacy group.
Another company that sponsored the dinner, Jones Day, represents one of the trade associations challenging the law, the National Federation of Independent Business.
Another sponsor was the pharmaceutical giant Pfizer Inc, for which huge funds are at stake in the process.
The dinner was held at a Washington hotel a few hours after a court discussion on the subject of the aforementioned case.
