Three abandoned dead bodies were found on the Cadereyta NL farm
A few hours before the discovery, military officials presented to the media 11 people who were detained in the area for offenses related to organized crime.
The bodies of three men murdered by gunshots to different parts of the body and head were found in an abandoned farmhouse in the municipality of Cadereyta Jiménez, Nuevo León.
The discovery occurred 1.5 kilometers from the road from Cadereyto to Santiago, at the level of an area known as El Castillo.
People who moved around these places noticed that the cottage with the beige-coffee fence had an open door from time to time.
