There was an eviction of a foreclosed house in which gigantic parties were held
The intruders appropriated 11 of the 13 apartments in the building in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the house at noon yesterday without resistance
All indications are that the nightmare experienced by the neighbors of number 51 Balmes Street is finally over.
Yesterday at noon, twelve people voluntarily left the building they were illegally occupying and where they organized gigantic parties that woke up the neighbors. They left the building by order of the court and without the police having to intervene.
After the operation, the lock on the door was changed to prevent a repeat of the situation.
&quot;From now on, the entrance will be guarded&quot;, declared the administrator.
The occupiers, who occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the given building - the rest are inhabited -, took away all the electrical and partly also the water equipment, in addition to painting the walls and leaving behind all kinds of rubbish, especially cans of alcoholic drinks.
The first three apartments hosted huge parties that lasted up to two days and woke up the other tenants.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that during the time the building was occupied, sales dropped by 80%.
The owner of the disco emphasizes that the occupants of the building were giving her unfair competition, because they sold drinks for 3 euros, while at the disco they cost 10.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment establishment had to respond to complaints from neighbors due to noise. However, the problems were not caused by the visitors of the disco, but by the residents of the occupied house and especially those who participated in the parties organized here, the frequency and intensity of which has increased in recent weeks, according to angry residents of the area.
The owner of the discotheque explained that the problems were so great that they even reached an agreement with the owner of the building and he has been forgiving her rent for nine months.
City police also confirmed that they had received multiple complaints from neighbors about the situation in recent weeks.
The head of the municipal group of the People&#39;s Party PP at City Hall, Alberto Fernández Díaz, demanded last week that &quot;the building be immediately evicted and thus put an end to the problems of civil coexistence suffered by the neighbors and to the destruction of the area&quot;.
The chairman of the People&#39;s Committee explained that only one floor had been occupied before the summer, but in recent months the occupiers had reached all floors of the building and almost all the apartments, and one of them had even been robbed.
In this regard, he added that &quot;it is necessary to put an end to impunity and be consistent when it comes to acts against civil responsibility that occurred in the building&quot;.
Yesterday, the city police also cleared a building in Nou Barris.
At 3:30 p.m., police arrived at 35 Mont-ral Street after being called by neighbors who saw four people entering the building.
All four were immediately arrested.
