A heavily exporting industry draws a large number of small and medium-sized specialized enterprises to international markets, creating jobs that cannot be transferred abroad.
If France decided to abandon nuclear, it would sacrifice a significant number of these small and medium-sized enterprises and lose the 6 billion euros a year that the country earns from exporting nuclear equipment and services.
What power plant owner would order a nuclear reactor designed to operate for 60 years while its manufacturer is scheduled for bankruptcy?
