In Chernobyl, the reactor design and inexcusable human error caused the drama.
In the case of Fukushima, some seem to forget that the accident was the result of two natural disasters of unprecedented scale that killed tens of thousands of people.
The nuclear industry will learn from this accident just as it did from the two previous ones.
The fruit of this step and the cooperation between French and German nuclear safety authorities, operators and designers is that the EPR type reactor represents a concept capable of withstanding such phenomena.
